com.siperian.sif.message.mrm

Class SetRecordStateRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianRequest
      • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianObjectRequest
        • com.siperian.sif.message.mrm.SetRecordStateRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SiperianObjectUidProvider, Serializable

    public class SetRecordStateRequest
extends SiperianObjectRequest
    Sets the record state of base object records identified by the specified keys.

    Required Parameters:

    • addRecordKey(RecordKey) - Add the key of a record for which the record state needs to be updated.
    • setRecordState(RecordState) - New record state for the records specified in the request.
    • SiperianObjectRequest.setSiperianObjectUid(String) - Specifies the package or base object to identify the record.

    Usage Example:

    The following example shows how to set the record state to QUEUED_FOR_MATCH for a record with ROWID_OBJECT key 782 using the ADDRESS_UPDATE package:

    SetRecordStateRequest request = new SetRecordStateRequest();
    request.setSiperianObjectUid("PACKAGE.ADDRESS_UPDATE");
    request.setRecordState(RecordState.QUEUED_FOR_MATCH);
    RecordKey recordKey = new RecordKey();
    recordKey.setRowid("782");
    request.addRecordKey(recordKey);
    SetRecordStateResponse response =
    (SetRecordStateResponse) sipClient.process(request);

    See Also:
    SetRecordStateResponse, RecordState, RecordKey, Serialized Form

    API Pair: SetRecordStateResponse

    API Group: Data Steward
